    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-05T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-05T14:00:00-05:00" n="294"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d294">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1194.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Sullivan</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-05T14:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 5, 1914, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your April 30, 7 p.m.</p>
                <p>Department requested Navy May 2nd to instruct Commander of <hi rend="italic"
                        >Petrel</hi> to request the opening of customhouse, Puerto Plata, and
                    continuance <pb facs="0346" n="230" xml:id="pg_230"/> of proper collection of
                    customs. He has further been instructed to advise this Department should this
                    request not be complied with, and to inform it of what action will be necessary
                    to bring compliance by authorities. He will see that all American and foreign
                    interests are given proper protection.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
